    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1969-02-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1969-02-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="273"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d273">
                <head>273. National Security Study Memorandum 14<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d273fn1">Source: National Archives, <persName corresp="#p_NRM1"
                            >Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials, <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                            >NSC</gloss> Files, Box 365, Subject Files, <gloss target="#t_NSSM1"
                            >NSSM</gloss>s 1–42. Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1969-02-05">February 5, 1969</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="to">
                    <head>TO</head>
                    <item>The Secretary of State</item>
                    <item>The Secretary of Defense</item>
                    <item>The Director for Central Intelligence</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_US1">U.S.</gloss> China Policy</item>
                </list>
                <p>The President has directed that a study be prepared on <gloss target="#t_US1"
                        >U.S.</gloss> Policy Towards China, on <gloss target="#t_US1">U.S.</gloss>
                    objectives and interests involved and the broad lines of appropriate <gloss
                        target="#t_US1">U.S.</gloss> policies. The study should incorporate
                    alternative views and interpretations of the issues involved. It should include
                    summary statements of the conceptions and policy lines of the previous
                    administration.</p>
                <p>The Study should include the following: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>The current status of <gloss target="#t_US1">U.S.</gloss> relations
                            with Communist China and the Republic of China;</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>The nature of the Chinese Communist threat and intentions in
                            Asia;</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>The interaction between <gloss target="#t_US1">U.S.</gloss> policy and
                            the policies of other major interested countries toward China;</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>Alternative <gloss target="#t_US1">U.S.</gloss> approaches on China
                            and their costs and risks.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>The President has directed that the <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss>
                    Interdepartmental Group for East Asia perform this study.</p>
                <p>The paper should be forwarded to the <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Review
                    Group by March 10.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Henry A. Kissinger</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
